A vintage-style architectural illustration depicting a family tree of interconnected filing cabinets in warm sepia and amber tones. The largest ornate wooden cabinet sits at the top like a patriarch, with brass handles and decorative carvings. Below it, connected by elegant curved lines resembling a genealogy chart, are two medium-sized cabinets with slightly different designs. Branching further down, smaller cabinets cascade in a hierarchical pattern, each one slightly simpler than its parent. One cabinet floats separately to the side, glowing softly with a golden aura, representing something special and cached. The background features aged parchment texture with subtle geometric patterns reminiscent of 1940s technical drawings. Dust motes float in warm afternoon light streaming from an unseen window, giving the scene a nostalgic, archival atmosphere.
